<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4401757>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. Differences in male genital structures (top, left posterolateral view; bottom, right ventrolateral view) among subspecies of Pterostichus eximius. Red, green, and blue arrows denote sublobe rv-2 on the endophallus, a swelling adjoining lobe ll on the endophallus, and the dorsal contour at the aedeagal subapex, respectively. Phylogenetic relationships inferred from these characters are shown." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4401757/files/figure.png" .

